1. Install Node.js
   Sass runs on Node.js, so you need it installed first

- Go to the Node.js official website
- Download the LTS version for Windows
- Run the installer and follow the setup instructions
- After installation, open Command Prompt and type:
  node -v
  npm -v

2. Install Sass via npm

- npm install -g sass

3. Verify Sass Installation

- To confirm Sass is installed, run sass --version

4. Using Sass

- You can now compile .scss or .sass files to CSS [sass input.css output.css]
- You can also watch files for changes: [sass --watch input.scss:output.css]
